Quote:  The <i>kupapa</i>, Maoris fighting on the British side, were variously known as `loyalists', `Queenites', and `the friendly natives'. ... [212] The motives of <i>kupapa</i> groups varied enormously ... <i>ibid.</i> 214 But throughout the period colonial units did ... have the support of `native auxilliaries' - the <i>kupapa</i>. <i>ibid.</i> 337 <i>kupapa</i> pro-government Maori (originally passive or neutral)
